The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the packing chromatic number of undirected and oriented generalized theta graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of graph coloring and partitioning also relates to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of distance and directed distance in the definition of packing chromatic number suggests a connection to graph theory and topology (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of tight bounds and characterization of graphs suggests a numerical analysis (cs.NA) aspect to the paper.
